6:<title>Brain — The coordination layer for AI agents</title>
107:/* SECTION UTILITIES */
108:.section { padding: 5rem 1.5rem; max-width: 1060px; margin: 0 auto; }
109:.section-wide { padding: 5rem 1.5rem; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }
112:.section h2, .section-wide h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.2vw, 2.3rem); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
113:.section h2.center, .section-wide h2.center { text-align: center; }
163:/* AGENT CARDS */
164:.agent-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; }
165:.agent-card {
169:.agent-card:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); transform: translateY(-2px); }
170:.agent-card::after {
173:.agent-card:nth-child(1)::after { background: var(--accent); }
174:.agent-card:nth-child(2)::after { background: var(--blue); }
175:.agent-card:nth-child(3)::after { background: var(--orange); }
176:.agent-card:nth-child(4)::after { background: var(--rose); }
177:.agent-card:nth-child(5)::after { background: var(--purple); }
178:.agent-card:nth-child(6)::after { background: var(--teal); }
179:.agent-card h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
180:.agent-role { font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
181:.agent-card p { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.55; }
219:/* CONCEPT GRID */
220:.concept-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; }
221:.concept {
225:.concept:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); }
226:.concept h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
227:.concept p { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 0.83rem; line-height: 1.55; }
229:/* OSS SECTION */
330:  .agent-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
358:    <a href="#agents">Agents</a>
362:    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/why-message-buses-arent-enough-building-multi-agent-knowledge-schack-0itnc/" target="_blank">Article</a>
368:<section class="hero">
372:  <p>Your agents have amnesia. They can't talk to each other. You spend 80% of your time as a high-paid secretary, copy-pasting context between them. Brain is the self-correcting knowledge graph that gives your agents shared memory, governed autonomy, and verifiable intent.</p>
377:</section>
382:    <div class="diagram-label">Architecture</div>
385:    <div class="d-row"><div class="d-tag">Agents</div><div class="d-boxes"><div class="d-box a">Architect</div><div class="d-box a">Strategist</div><div class="d-box a">Management</div><div class="d-box a">Coding · MCP</div><div class="d-box a">Observer</div></div></div>
398:<section class="section reveal" id="problem">
400:  <h2>You are the integration layer<br>between your AI agents</h2>
401:  <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">You already use AI agents. Your coding agent writes your code. Your chat assistant helps you think through architecture. Your editor agent autocompletes. But none of them share context.</p>
403:    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Copy error logs from CI into your coding agent</li>
404:    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Relay architecture decisions from a chat into your codebase</li>
409:  <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:1rem;">Every agent you add makes it worse. Brain fixes this — not by replacing your agents, but by giving them shared memory.</p>
410:</section>
415:<section class="section reveal">
416:  <div class="tag tag-center">The architecture</div>
417:  <h2 class="center">Why a graph, not a message bus</h2>
418:  <p class="subtitle">Most platforms try "agent swarms" — agents messaging agents. That creates a game of telephone where instructions get distorted. The graph is the single source of truth.</p>
420:    <thead><tr><th>Approach</th><th>Agent swarms / message buses</th><th>Knowledge graph (Brain)</th></tr></thead>
424:      <tr><td>Coordination</td><td>Agents message agents (telephone game)</td><td>Agents read/write to shared truth</td></tr>
432:</section>
436:<!-- AGENTS -->

